<title type="html"><![CDATA[New &quot;resizable&quot; attribute]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=105&amp;p=424#p424"><![CDATA[
draggable=&quot;&quot; is in HTML because there are several events related to dragging and you usually want to do something specific when the user drags something, e.g. add an item to the shopping cart.<br /><br />Resize however is purely visual, and you normally wouldn't do anything in response to something being resized.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4">zcorpan</a> — Tue Sep 11, 2007 9:23 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
